parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine fires can cause complete destruction of the vehicle, putting the occupants and other road users at risk of injury or death.
symptoms: Vehicle catches fire shortly after cold start
complete consumption of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the distributor cap can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off, increasing the risk of accidents, especially in rainy conditions.
symptoms: Vehicle cuts off completely when it's raining or water gets into the distributor through the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning fuel system can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Gasping or hesitation in the fuel intake when accelerating or cruising at high speeds
sudden drop in speedometer reading.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine cylinder head failure can cause engine overheating, leading to costly repairs, and potentially causing accidents due to loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Engine overheating
emitting foul odors
antifreeze leaking into engine oil
cylinder failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt latch can compromise the safety of the occupants in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle will not latch properly
the seat belt buckle breaks
the seat belt latch is difficult to engage
the seat belt latch is stuck
the seat belt buckle comes undone while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and noise can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle, as well as inconvenience and distress to the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle makes a horrible and bumping noise when in parking gear
the transmission slips into another gear without warning
the vehicle rolls back unexpectedly
the vehicle hits another object or vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tread separation can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities. The sudden failure of the tire can also cause damage to the vehicle's underbody and exhaust system.
symptoms: The tread of the tire separates from the tire casing while driving
often at high speeds
leaving the tire still inflated with the steel belts showing. The vehicle may experience an uncontrolled skid
and the driver may lose control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the spare tire cable can cause the spare tire to fall off the vehicle, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The spare tire cable rusts off
causing the spare tire to fall off the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A corroded secondary throttle plate on the carburetor can cause the vehicle to suddenly accelerate out of control, leading to accidents, property damage, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the throttle linkage sticks against the secondary throttle plate
the vehicle runs out of control
the vehicle accelerates even when the driver is not pressing the accelerator pedal.
